The test on Well # 3 in the PETREL Field consisted of two
Arawdown periods followed by a buildup Bottom hole pressure
was measured by Anerada gauges .

buildup data . At the same time a LOGLOG plot of the REAL

o GAS POTENTIAL FUNCTION M ( p ) versus elapsed time was made

Ng out using pressures p instead of gas potentials M ( p ) .The

shape cf the log1log plot was characteristic of a homogeneous

system . An initial match was found on the FLOFETROL TYPECURVE
kaa for a well with wellbore storage and skin ( HOMOGENEOUS
RESERVOIR ) . This match indicated the point at which radial
flow was established in the system ana thus indicatea the
start cf the straight line for semilog analysis .
